Four different technologies are studied in this work, three of which are lithium-based technologies (NMC, LFP and LIC) and the remaining one is a NiMH cell, as compiled in Table 1. Their nominal capacity (C



                                 N


                        ) varies from 0.8 to 3.5 Ah and their nominal voltage (V



                                 N


                        ) from 1.2 to 4.2 V. The NiMH, NMC and LFP cells are cylindrical, while the LIC is a pouch cell, as shown in Fig. 2. The main operating conditions for each cell are summarized in Table 2. They have different standard charge and discharge methods, as well as temperature ranges. A total of 40 cells were utilized in this study; some of them for characterization experiments and others for aging experiments, as explained in following Sections 4.2 and 4.3.
